What are elements of the redistribution-with-growth policy approach? The redistribution-with-growth policy approach is a policy approach that focuses on reducing income inequality and promoting economic growth. The approach typically involves using tax and spending policies to redistribute income from high-income to low-income households. The goal of the approach is to improve economic outcomes for all households, not just high-income households.
Which is an element of the redistribution-with-growth policy approach, increased education or land reform? Increased education would be an element of the redistribution-with-growth policy approach.
